  "text": "The Y-maze protocol was adapted from [CITATION_1] . The apparatus was a three-armed wooden structure, painted black. Each arm measured 10.5 by 48 cm, with 15 cm high walls. The structure was elevated off the ground, and there were numerous visual cues surrounding the maze to be used for spatial orientation. The floor was covered in bedding, which was mixed between trials to prevent odours being used as non-spatial cues.",
